display_name = "Virus"
thumbnail = ExtResource("2_ub3ss")
story_text = Array[String](["The Center for Advanced Mathematics for Energy Research Applications developed their Multi-Tiered Iterative Phasing (M-TIP) algorithm for X-ray free-electron laser (XFEL) data. This specimen shows the result of an investigation of the structural features of nanoscale viruses using M-TIP. The rice dwarf virus (RDV) and the PR772 bacteriophage virus particles, approximately 70 nm in diameter, were aerosolized and introduced into the XFEL beam using a gas dynamic virtual nozzle and aerodynamic lens stack. The scattering data were collected at the Linac Coherent Light Source (LCLS) with pnCCD detectors, achieving a resolution of ~12 nm at the detector edge.", "Over 3 million diffraction patterns were recorded, from which high-intensity single-particle hits were extracted and categorized by size to minimize the effects of polydispersity. The final dataset included 332 RDV and 566 PR772 diffraction patterns.", "The significance of this data lies in its unprecedented structural richness. Using fluctuation X-ray scattering (FXS) and angular cross-correlation functions (CCFs), the researchers extracted detailed fingerprints of the full 3D structure of individual virus particles. These correlation maps go beyond traditional small-angle X-ray scattering (SAXS) by incorporating higher-order information, which enabled the identification of nanoscale structural deviations from ideal icosahedral symmetry.", "The analysis revealed that even small distortions (as little as 3% compression) significantly affect the correlation data and provided evidence of anisotropic internal density distributions. This level of detail is critical because such asymmetries are often lost in conventional crystallography, which averages over symmetric orientations.", "Ultimately, this virus data demonstrates the power of angular correlations at XFELs to uncover fine structural details without requiring crystallization or symmetry assumptions, paving the way for the investigation of biological nanostructures."])
